&lt;li&gt;Apply and maintain the firm’s standard document templates across all document types; update templates when instructed by legal counsel.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Format complex multi-schedule agreements, annexures, and exhibits in compliance with the firm’s house style.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Standard form Documents preparation and management: Embassy &amp;amp; Consular Letters; No Objection Letters (NOC); Salary / Employment Certificates; Experience &amp;amp; Reference Letters; Board Resolutions (Standard Form); Powers of Attorney and Regulatory Filing Cover Letters&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Administrative functions: arrange translations, notarisations, legalisations, PO requests&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and update the legal function&#39;s document management system, ensuring all executed agreements, corporate documents, regulatory filings, and correspondence are filed correctly.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct quarterly database audits to identify and remediate gaps or expired entries and report findings to the Head of Legal.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT WE LOOK FOR IN YOU&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
