&lt;li&gt;An international firm or financial services background is an advantage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Secondary or post-secondary qualification in legal studies, business administration, or a related field; a legal secretary or paralegal certification (e.g., CILEX Foundation, ILSPA) is an advantage but not required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated experience preparing embassy letters, NOCs, employment certificates, and similar standard-form correspondence independently.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing a contracts register or legal document database.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with DocuSign (or equivalent electronic signature platform) is required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced proficiency with Google Workspace and Microsoft Office suite.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional attention to detail: errors in legal documents carry real consequences and will not be tolerated.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Discretion and confidentiality as default behaviour: the Legal Secretary will handle highly sensitive commercial, personnel, and regulatory information.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
