&lt;div class=&quot;jobDescription&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;jobCell__left&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an experienced Senior Payroll Accountant to take ownership of payroll accounting and payroll-related operations across multiple jurisdictions. As part of the Accounting team, you will be responsible for payroll calculations for selected entities, payroll-related reconciliations, coordination of external payroll providers and service partners, and ensuring the accuracy of personnel-related expenses. You will work closely with HR, Legal, Treasury, Tax, and external providers to support a growing international workforce.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is ideal for someone with a strong accounting background who understands payroll processes, enjoys improving operational efficiency, and is comfortable working in a dynamic international environment where processes continue to evolve.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU’LL BE DOING&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Calculate payroll and personnel-related expenses for assigned entities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate payroll-related activities across multiple jurisdictions and legal entities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with HR, Legal, Treasury and Tax teams to ensure accurate and timely payroll processing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform payroll-related account reconciliations and support month-end closing activities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage communication with external payroll providers, accounting firms, EORs, and other service providers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review and oversee payroll calculations prepared by outsourced payroll teams and external providers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure payroll data is complete, accurate, and delivered within established deadlines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with payroll software and related systems to support payroll operations and reporting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create, document, and improve payroll processes, controls, and workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify inefficiencies and implement process enhancements to improve operational effectiveness and scalability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support payroll-related audits by providing required payroll documentation, reconciliations, and supporting schedules&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Resolve payroll-related issues and manage ad hoc operational requests in a timely manner&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT WE LOOK FOR IN YOU&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6+ years of accounting experience, including significant exposure to payroll accounting and personnel-related expenses&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of payroll accounting, reconciliations, accruals, controls, and month-end close processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with external payroll providers, outsourced teams, EORs and other service providers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;General understanding of payroll-related tax and compliance requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience supporting payroll operations across multiple jurisdictions. Familiarity with payroll requirements in the UAE and UK is an advantage; willingness to learn and navigate country-specific requirements is essential&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to establish, streamline, and improve processes in a fast-growing or evolving environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical skills, attention to detail, and problem-solving capabilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent organizational skills with the ability to manage multiple priorities and meet tight deadlines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with payroll software, EOR platforms and ERP systems (e.g. Oracle NetSuite)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Team player with a proactive, hands-on, and solution-oriented mindset&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work under pressure while maintaining a high level of accuracy and attention to detail&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluent English, both written and spoken&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
